#. type: TP
#: doc/tin.1:3801
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<ORGANIZATION>"
msgstr "B<ORGANIZATION>"

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/tin.1:3808
msgid ""
"Set the article header field ''Organization:'' to the contents of the "
"variable instead of the system default. If it points to a readable file a "
"random line from that file will be used. If reading news on an Apollo "
"DomainOS machine the environment variable $B<NEWSORG> has to be used instead "
"of $B<ORGANIZATION>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: doc/tin.1:3808
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<NEWSORG (DomainOS)>"
msgstr "B<NEWSORG (DomainOS)>"

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/tin.1:3811
msgid "DomainOS specific, same as $B<ORGANIZATION> on other OSs (see above)."
msgstr ""
"DomainOS spezifisch, wie $B<ORGANIZATION> auf anderen Betriebssystemen "
"(siehe oben)."

#. type: TP
#: doc/tin.1:3811
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<REPLYTO>"
msgstr "B<REPLYTO>"

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/tin.1:3816
msgid ""
"Set the article header field ''Reply-To:'' to the return address specified "
"by the variable. This is useful if you wish to receive replies at a "
"different address."
msgstr ""
"Setzt die »Reply-To:«-Kopfzeile auf die in der Variable angegebene "
"Rücksendeadresse. Dies ist nützlich, wenn Sie Antworten an eine andere "
"Adresse erhalten möchten."

#. type: TP
#: doc/tin.1:3816
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<NAME>"
msgstr "B<NAME>"

#. type: Plain text
#: doc/tin.1:3820
msgid ""
"Overrides the full name given in the gecos-field in I</etc/passwd>, see also "
"B<mail_address>."
